I’ve been ordering take-out from here for a while. It’s priced about the same as most other S. Brooklyn sushi places I’ve eaten at/ordered from. Quality of fish is pretty good and it’s fresh. Delivery is usually on time, except once when they didn’t tell me it was going to take over an hour.. the reason I am giving 3 stars and tempted to give 2, is their delivery guy. The one that they use most of the time, the older guy.. I dread having to see him right before I eat; it almost ruins my appetite. He is so rude. And I can deal with his sour face and no hello or goodbye or thank you for the tip, but he even goes as far as too shake his head and mutter under his breath sometimes. I think he is perhaps unhappy with the tip, because there really is no other reason for this rudeness. And I never give less than $2 (for a small order). His attitude makes me not want to give him ANY tip at all, but I just can’t make myself do that. I feel bad. But someone really needs to make him understand that the nature of tipping is that it is completely up to the customer and isn’t obligatory and no one owes him anything. I am sure he doesn’t make much money, but this is definitely not the way to remedy that situation. I hope they either get a new delivery guy soon, or teach this one some very basic manners, because it does make a difference (!!!)
